en_content:
AGI - Hundreds of thousands of people, according to some even 1.5 million, have crowded the beach of Copacabana, in Rio de Janeiro, > and many others have assisted from the sea, aboard dozen boats, to a "historic" free concert with which Madonna has concluded his Celebration Tour.
The 65-year-old "pop page" appeared on the stage of over 800 square meters towards 23 of last night, 3 at night in Italy, after crossing a catwalk built specifically by Copacabana Palace, where she lived for a few days, and performed for more than 2 hours > enchanting all her most famous songs and changing constantly of dress. The Rio concert concluded its "Celebration Tour", 80 concerts in Europe, North America and Mexico with which he wanted to consecrate 40 years of career >, retracing successes and musical metamorphoses and personality, scandals and provocations, from pop to electronic music.
<div </div
&nbsp;
With many of her children, who accompanied her in music or dance, Madonna was also reached on the Rio stage by many famous guests, with the background of the Brazilian flag. When he performed his hit "Vogue", he was accompanied by the 31-year-old Brazilian singer Anitta, known for having made known in the world the carioca funk, soundtrack of the favelas of Rio. With Madonna she also sang the pop star and drag queen Pabllo Vittar, > while a group of children from the schools of samba in Rio played percussion.&nbsp;
